latestPosts.caption:
✨ Best Foods to Boost Collagen (Naturally!) ✨
Watch to see the top animal-based vs. plant-based foods that help your body produce and protect collagen 💪

🧬 Animal-Based Sources
🥚 Eggs
🐟 Fatty fish
🍗 Chicken skin
🍲 Bone broth
In these foods, you’ll find different ways to support collagen production: amino acids like glycine and proline, omega-3s, and natural sources of the compound itself.

🌿 Plant-Based Boosters
🍅 Tomatoes
🥬 Leafy greens
🍓 Berries
🥑 Avocados
These foods have a variety of nutrients to support collagen synthesis and production, like: vitamin C, antioxidants, and healthy fats to help protect and strengthen your skin from within.

Want that glow from the inside out? Start with what’s on your plate. 💧✨

Feeling stressed? Your plate might be part of the solution 🧘‍♀️🍽️

These foods help lower cortisol—the body’s main stress hormone—naturally:

🥬 Magnesium-rich picks like leafy greens & nuts can relax muscles and calm the nervous system
🐟 Omega-3s from salmon, chia, and walnuts can reduce inflammation and promote mental clarity
🍫 Antioxidant-rich treats like berries, dark chocolate, and green tea can fight stress at the cellular level

Eat to feel calm, focused, and more in control—because your body and mind deserve peace 💚

#kettleandfire #cortisol #lowercortisol #omega3 #magnesium #antioxidant

latestPosts.caption:
Let food be your medicine.

When we nourish our bodies with simple, whole foods, they can help us think clearer, move easier, and feel better. 

Eating for health should be both easy and delicious!

#foodasmedicine #kettleandfirewellness #healfromwithin #kettleandfirekitchen #wholefoodhealing

When inflammation flares up, your gut craves calm, not chaos 🧘‍♀️🔥💚

These healing foods help ease the fire and nourish from within:
🥑 Avocados – full of healthy fats and fiber to gently support digestion
🌶️ Peppers – rich in antioxidants like vitamin C to fight inflammation
🍲 Bone broth – packed with collagen and amino acids to repair the gut lining
🟠 Turmeric – a natural anti-inflammatory that supports gut and immune health
🐟 Sardines – loaded with omega-3s to calm the gut and support your microbiome
🍒 Cherries – full of polyphenols that reduce oxidative stress and inflammation

Simple, whole foods can do powerful things when your body needs to heal 💫

#GutHealth #AntiInflammatoryFoods #BoneBrothBenefits #HealingFromWithin #InflammationSupport

🧡 Eat More Orange Foods for a Natural Glow 🧡

Carrots, sweet potatoes, oranges, turmeric, bone broth… these vibrant foods aren’t just pretty - they’re packed with things like: beta-carotene, vitamin C, and/or antioxidants and anti-inflammatories that can nourish your skin, support your immune system, and fight inflammation from the inside out ✨

Add more orange to your plate and your body just may thank you with clearer skin, better energy, and a natural, healthy glow 🍊🥕🔥
